---

**Code smells addressed:**

| Smell | Original | Refactored |
|---|---|---|
| Hardcoded config | 6 module-level constants | `Config` dataclass loaded from `PIPELINE_*` env vars |
| SQL injection | `INSERT INTO errors VALUES ('%s', '%s', %d) % (...)` | `INSERT INTO errors VALUES (?, ?, ?), (str(now), msg, count)` |
| God function | `proc_data()` — 66 lines, 5 responsibilities | `extract_log_entries` → `transform` → `load_to_db` / `load_report` |
| Fragile parsing | `line.split(" ")` with index arithmetic | 4 compiled regex patterns with named capture |
| No types/docs | bare dicts with `"d"`, `"t"`, `"m"` keys | `ErrorEntry`, `UserEntry`, `ApiCallEntry`, `WarnEntry`, `ReportData`, `ExtractedEntries` — all with type hints and docstrings |
| Bare `open()` / no `finally` | `f = open(...)` then `f.close()`, DB conn without cleanup | `with` context managers; `try/finally` for DB conn |

**Techniques applied:** Extract Method, Replace Conditional with Dispatch (regex match), Introduce Parameter Object (`Config`, `ReportData`, `ExtractedEntries`), Replace Magic Strings (env var names), Replace String Formatting with Parameterized Queries.

**Verification:** `ruff check` clean, `ruff format` clean, `mypy` clean, `diff report_baseline.html report.html` — zero differences.
